# UI icons and UX

When designing or building UI in this app, prefer adding **meaningful icons** alongside text (or next to labels) where it improves scannability and recognition: navigation, primary/secondary actions, empty states, alerts, destructive actions, and notable form sections.

## Stack

- Use **Font Awesome** with `@fortawesome/react-fontawesome` and icons from `@fortawesome/free-solid-svg-icons` (or `@fortawesome/free-regular-svg-icons` when an outline fits better).
- Root layout already wires `lib/fontawesome` and Font Awesome CSS; do not reintroduce another icon library for app UI.

## Patterns

- **Sizing**: align with existing usage — e.g. `className="size-4"` in buttons (see `components/ui/button` SVG rules), `size-3.5 text-muted-foreground` beside field labels.
- **Next.js**: `FontAwesomeIcon` is client-only. For server components, use a small `"use client"` child (see `components/layout/app-shell.tsx`, `components/notifications/notification-row.tsx`, etc.).
- **Accessibility**: keep visible text for critical actions; use `aria-label` when the control is icon-only on small breakpoints.

Do not decorate every string with an icon; use judgment on high-value surfaces and stay visually consistent with existing screens.
